claim.claim-text:
A computer-implemented method, comprising:
receiving, via a processor, a request to analyze a tag indicating content to be presented at a content presentation service, wherein the tag comprises a link to the content and a tracking pixel associated with the content;
identifying, via the processor, criteria associated with the content presentation service;
determining, via the processor, whether the tag meets the criteria; and
providing, via the processor, a user notification indicating whether the tag meets the criteria.

A tangible, non-transitory, machine-readable medium, comprising machine-readable instructions that, when executed by one or more processors of a machine, cause the machine to:
receive a request to analyze a tag indicating content to be presented at a content presentation service, wherein the tag comprises a link to the content and a tracking pixel associated with the content;
identify criteria associated with the content presentation service;
determine whether the tag meets the criteria; and
provide a user notification indicating whether the tag meets the criteria.
